The paper discusses algorithms for solving $k$-best enumeration problems in graphs, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for efficiently storing and manipulating graph data. The problem of finding $k$ shortest paths and $k$ smallest spanning trees involves combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques such as dynamic programming and branch-and-bound algorithms. The problem of finding $k$ best matchings in weighted graphs involves computational geometry (cs.CG) techniques such as geometric algorithms for matching problems. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques such as reinforcement learning for solving $k$-best enumeration problems.
